<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One funny thing that could happen to you is th=
at your employer could promise to pay you $680,000 over 16 months, meaning =
about $42,500 per month, but then in the contract, instead of typing =E2=80=
=9Cwe will pay you $680,000 in monthly installments over 16 months,=E2=80=
=9D they might type =E2=80=9Cwe will pay you $680,000 per month for 16 mont=
hs.=E2=80=9D That would be better, for you, though you=E2=80=99d definitely=
 have to go to court about it. Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/29572408.263505/aHR0cHM6Ly9sYXdwcm9mZXNzb3JzLnR5cGVwYW=
QuY29tL2NvbnRyYWN0c3Byb2ZfYmxvZy8yMDIyLzExL2plZmYtbGlwc2hhdy1vbi1zY3JpdmVuZ=
XJzLWVycm9ycy0uaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5556e904" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> law profe=
ssor Jeff Lipshaw</a>=C2=A0on a real case:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A Chinese tech company has a U.S. subsidiary. =
=C2=A0The subsidiary hires a senior executive on a fixed term three-year co=
ntract. =C2=A0Along the way, the parent company=E2=80=99s founder in China,=
 wants the executive fired. =C2=A0Negotiations for the separation ensue, in=
 English and in Mandarin, but the contract is in English, drafted by the su=
bsidiary=E2=80=99s outside lawyers in Virginia. =C2=A0Drafts get circulated=
 internally, but it=E2=80=99s clear that the executive, at the very least, =
is going to get the balance of his salary for the remainder of the three-ye=
ar contract: =E2=80=9CThe Company agrees to make severance payments to you =
in the form of continuation of your base salary in effect on the Separation=
 Date for sixteen (16) months.=E2=80=9D =C2=A0That total would have been $6=
80,000.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Then things go terribly wrong (internally). =
=C2=A0The outside lawyer changes the draft to this: =E2=80=9C[T]he Company =
agrees to make monthly severance payments to you in the amount of $ _____ f=
or sixteen (16) months.=E2=80=9D =C2=A0The in-house gets the drafts and typ=
es into the blank =E2=80=9C$680,000=E2=80=9D, creating a putative obligatio=
n of $10,880,000.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This went to court and, as of last month, the =
executive won =E2=80=94 he gets the $11 million =E2=80=94=C2=A0though that =
could still be appealed.=C2=A0</p>
